    aiDescription: "Seasonal waterside sports facility offering kayak & SUP rentals, plus croquet & a party raft.",
    reviews: [{"authorName": "Юлия Щербина", "authorPhoto": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpxkHte5CgzABAWTBG14xi2IlCUDUa_IHs-0ivLX6QjvRvS2gA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", "rating": 4, "text": "This is an open-air swimming spot not far from the center. There’s a small pool for young children, as well as some sprinklers and water features. You can also swim in the river, where there’s a pontoon for entering the water but be aware that it gets deep very quickly. Even on a 35°C day the water stays quite cool. It’s easy to find both shade and sunny areas to lie down. The place also has a sports zone with volleyball, changing rooms, toilets, and spots where you can buy food and drinks. Overall, it’s a pretty good and affordable place to spend a hot day - around 120 CZK , but can be pretty crowded.", "relativeTime": "4 months ago"}, {"authorName": "Taher Kebab", "authorPhoto": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVI-Y-n4mBCkT_6kkCpjqo5jjHnXPEgkIdm_Vpcm1lejA9Nkzic=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", "rating": 5, "text": "Amazing place, clean , has sport facilities like ( volleyball, table tennis , basketball and you can borrow Padel surf board )\nHas food and almost everything, good prices.\nWe paid for entry: 120 kc each ( 5€ )\nWe payed for Half an a hour of table tennis 75kc ( 3 € )\nI saw the lady charging someone else 100 for half an hour ( 4€ ) either she gave me discount or she overcharged him or I misheard", "relativeTime": "9 months ago"}, {"authorName": "Anna Ganzelevitch", "authorPhoto": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKfUI7EMzBR6_paYQUVo0sdljbWPn7dS6Hot7Yprd4mr4VVVGdOg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", "rating": 5, "text": "amazing memories at this place! such a gem and chill vibe. It’s gonna be even prettier when the bridge is finally done.", "relativeTime": "7 months ago"}, {"authorName": "Olga", "authorPhoto": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUr19HuRO06AxKAZZuhfl3ceVo8YLPuQn1GzIebeY22i_E1FN_d=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5", "rating": 5, "text": "I didn’t investige all the area, it’s big) I was with a 3 year old son so we spent time in kids area. It was nice, my son was screaming from happiness. It’s clean, there are toilets, changing rooms, changing rooms for babies, a small cafe and very nice swimming pools for kids of different ages. We were there on Monday, it was not busy, there was enough space for everyone.", "relativeTime": "a year ago"}, {"authorName": "Wess Grumble", "authorPhoto": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHsyjC55xEWpzXljxQ5BYKYDIi67Uqbl3DzYezMQrr8bStnduByA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3", "rating": 5, "text": "Nice to relax on a very hot summer's day, 10 minutes from the city centre.  Take a dip in the river, play ping-pong or volley ball.\nPlenty of places with nice food and cold drinks. (Beer).  A hot day well spent if you go there.  Especially after a long party day.", "relativeTime": "2 years ago"}],
